# Public env for Vite — single file for this app (no separate .env.example / .env.development).
# Only `VITE_*` variables are exposed to client code.
#
# Local dev: leave VITE_API_URL unset so requests use same-origin `/api/*`.
# Vite proxies `/api` to Express at http://127.0.0.1:5000 (see vite.config.ts).
#
# If you set VITE_API_URL=http://localhost:5000, add your storefront origin to the backend
# `CLIENT_URL` or you may hit CORS errors.
#
# Production / cross-origin API (no trailing slash):
# VITE_API_URL=https://api.example.com

# Razorpay Checkout public key — must match the key id configured in the backend.
VITE_RAZORPAY_KEY_ID=rzp_test_Snh6GjGsBzuwL6
